\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A global de-centralized / OTC market for currencies trading which operates
 24/7.
 It is the largest and the most liquid market in the world.
 It is very large and has grown with globalization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are many types of contracts (spot, future, derivaties), with 
\series bold
swaps 
\series default
the most popular.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\series bold
exchange rate
\series default
 is defined as the number of dometic currency units per single unit of a
 foreign currency.
 The domestic currency depreciates (appreciates) when the exchange rate
 increases (decreases).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Looking at the EUR/USD rate over time in can be seen that there was a depreciati
on of USD until the 2008 crisis, followed by a reversal afterwards (problems
 in Europe began to arise - crises in Greece, Ireland, Portugal).
